<title>HONG KONG: China Motor Bus interim net up sharply.</title>
<headline>China Motor Bus interim net up sharply.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-02-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ended December 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   1,849.0     vs 38.0</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    21.0	  vs 21.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  101.43 gain vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    855.32	vs 17.66</p>
<p>    Turnover		     411.56	vs 376.77</p>
<p>    Company name		 China Motor Bus Co Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  March 17-18</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   April 1</p>
<p>NOTE - China Motor Bus operates franchised public buses in Hong Kong. It declares a special dividend of HK$1.60 vs $0.16.</p>
<p>The exceptional item for the period represents the partial recognition of deferred profit arising from property disposal.</p>
<p>The group pays two interim and one final dividend a year.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong News Room (852) 2843 6368</p>
